<node id="article:2000_162">
  <data key="d0">Article</data>
  <data key="d2">Restructuring of the Electric Power Industry</data>
  <data key="d3"></data>
  <data key="d4">This talk begins by reviewing the historical developments and motivation that have led to the restructuring of the electric power industry. A comparison is made of the conventional electric monopolies and the new models based on market- driven electricity markets. In particular, pool and bilateral contract based market models will be presented and analyzed. Some of the current related research activities at McGill and elsewhere are also reviewed. A brief overview is given of the principal inde- pendent system operators in use today in North America and their main features. Finally, the talk suggests a number of business and research opportunities in the field of competitive power systems. Anais do XIII Congresso Brasileiro de Automática - CBA 2000 11 a 14 de setembro de 2000 - Florianópolis - SC - Brasil</data>
  <data key="d5">2000/162.pdf</data>
</node>
